Write a function that takes the base and height of a triangle and return its area.

Examples
triArea(3, 2) ➞ 3 
triArea(7, 4) ➞ 14 
triArea(10, 10) ➞ 50
Test Cases
triArea(3, 2) ➞ 3
triArea(5, 4) ➞ 10
triArea(10, 10) ➞ 50
triArea(0, 60) ➞ 0
triArea(12, 11) ➞ 66

solution:

function triArea(x,h){
	return x*h/2;
}
